  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Higher model risk drives stricter credibility requirements; Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed. This package conforms to the Minimal profile. A Requirement object is defined inline within the narrative context and referenced by the hasDecisionRecord rationale, but no top-level bindsRequirement link is emitted — constituting the W-SI-02 structural gap.",
